  "texts": [
    "Advancements in legal technology: from COMPAS and E-discovery systems to AI-driven legal softwareIn the evolving field of legal technology, the Correctional Offender Management Profiling for Alternative Sanctions (COM-PAS) emerges as a pivotal yet contentious innovation.",
    "Employed by adjudicators for its predictive capabilities, COMPAS symbolises the potential advancements and inherent challenges within legal tech.",
    "However, its introduction into the legal system has been met with mixed reactions, highlighting significant ethical and effectiveness concerns [22].",
    "This complexity mirrors the broader dialogue in legal tech adoption, where diverse perspectives and ethical considerations converge [23].",
    "Acknowledging COMPAS at this juncture is essential, setting the stage for a deeper examination of the controversies it embodies and emphasising the necessity for a nuanced analysis of both the opportunities and pitfalls presented by such technological tools in legal contexts."
  ]
}